verbose_text: A two-section questionnaire including demographic characteristics (such as age, gender, marital status, occupation, educational level, economic and employment status; Body Mass Index (BMI), Ejection fraction (EF), history of re-hospitalization, and medical information (including records of diabetes mellitus, hypertension, high cholesterol levels and smoking), and questions based on HPM constructs (97 items) to adopt self care behaviors was distributed among the patients to collect data.
